item.title: CVE-2022-1829|2024-08-03T00:16:59.969Z -- unknown -- inline%20google%20maps
item.description: The Inline Google Maps WordPress plugin through 5.11 does not have CSRF check in place when updating its settings, which could allow attackers to make a logged in admin change them via a CSRF attack, and lead to Stored Cross-Site Scripting due to the lack of sanitisation and escaping
